    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-20T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-20T07:00:00-05:00" n="149"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.623/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-20T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 20, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 20—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. Your 26, March 19, 6 p.m. Verbally informed Foreign Office this morning as
                    instructed. Foreign Office repeated information to Schacht’s<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d149fn17">Hjalmar Schacht, German Minister for Economic
                        Affairs.</note> office and has now verbally informed Embassy of latter’s
                    approval of reply which will be returned to Foreign Office promptly and is
                    expected to reach Embassy on Monday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
